This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on abstractive text summarization. Additionally, the use of Attentional Encoder-Decoder Recurrent Neural Networks is a common technique in this sub-field. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). 

The use of novel models to address critical problems in summarization suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper involves modeling the hierarchy of sentence-to-word structure, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

Finally, the paper proposes a new dataset and establishes performance benchmarks, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
